{{no footnotes|date=March 2017}} [[File:Boris Pozern.jpg|right|thumb|Boris Pozern]] '''Boris Pavlovich Pozern''' (7 July 1882 – 25 February 1939) was a Soviet politician. He was born in [[Nizhny Novgorod]]. He was a member of the [[Russian Constituent Assembly]] of 1918. He was a member of the [[Central Committee elected by the 17th Congress of the All-Union Communist Party (Bolsheviks)]]. During the [[Great Purge]], he was arrested on 9 July 1938 and later executed by firing squad in [[Moscow]]. After the death of [[Joseph Stalin]], he was rehabilitated in 1957.
