{{Infobox War on Terror detainee | name = Mohamed Bensakhria | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | arrest_date = 2001 | arrest_place = [[Alicante]], [[Spain]] | arresting_authority= [[Spanish police]] | release_date = | release_place = | death_date = | death_place = | citizenship = [[Algeria|Algerian]] | detained_at = | id_number = | group = | alias = | charge = | penalty = 10 years | status = released | csrt_summary = | csrt_transcript= | occupation = | spouse = | parents = | children = }}
'''Mohamed Bensakhria''' is an [[Algeria]]n citizen, sentenced in [[France]] to 10 years in prison for his role in the 2000 [[Strasbourg Cathedral bombing plot]] on December 16, 2004.<ref name="cbs">{{cite news|title=France Convicts Islamic Militants|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2004/12/16/terror/main661554.shtml|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=15 October 2011}}</ref> He is suspected of having had close links to [[Osama bin Laden]].<ref name=CNN/><ref name=theguardian/>
He was arrested in [[Alicante]] on June 22, 2001. According to Spanish authorities, he was the leader of the Meliani group. Bensakhria's group was, according to Spanish authorities, funded by bin Laden.<ref name=theguardian>{{cite news|title=Spanish police arrest Bin Laden suspect|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2001/jun/23/gilestremlett|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=15 October 2011|location=London|first=Giles|last=Tremlett|date=23 June 2001}}</ref> He had lived in Alicante for a period, after escaping from German police. The German police had uncovered a terror plot in December, and dismantled the group Bensakhria is believed to have led.<ref name=CNN>{{cite news|title=Suspected Bin Laden associate to be extradited|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2001-06-25/world/spain.extradition_1_extradition-arrest-warrant-spain-s-national-court?_s=PM:WORLD|publisher=CNN|accessdate=15 October 2011|date=25 June 2001}}</ref>
