[[File:Sergio del Valle.jpg|thumb|right|Sergio del Valle Jiménez, 1986]] '''Sergio del Valle Jiménez''' (15 April 1927&mdash;15 November 2007) was a high-ranking [[Cuba]]n military and government official who served as [[Military of Cuba|army chief of staff]] during the [[Cuban Missile Crisis|1962 Missile Crisis]] and headed various cabinet ministries during the 1960s, 1970s and 1980s.
==Biography== A physician by training, Sergio del Valle became a part of the movement against the government of [[Fulgencio Batista]] in the 1950s and, by 1957, was fighting in [[Fidel Castro]]'s rebel army's second column under the leadership of [[Camilo Cienfuegos]]. After Castro took power, del Valle served in a number of top positions, most notably his key military post at the time of the Missile Crisis. In subsequent decades, he was Interior Minister (1968&ndash;79) and Public Health Minister (1979&ndash;86).
Sergio del Valle died in [[Havana]] at the age of 80. <ref>[http://www.plenglish.com/article.asp?ID=%7BB298803B-F7A9-41AF-BD20-F00CA5462940%7D)&language=EN ''Prensa Latina'' obituary: "Cuban Republic Hero Dies"]</ref> <ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/17/world/americas/16cnd-delvalle.html?ref=world ''New York Times'' obituary: "Sergio del Valle, a Castro Stalwart, Dies"]</ref>
==See also== *[[Ministry of the Interior (Cuba)|Ministry of the Interior of Cuba]]
